def summarize_dataset(df, dataset_name):
    print(f"Dataset: {dataset_name}")
    print(f"Total Rows (Food Items): {df.shape[0]}")
    print(f"Total Columns: {df.shape[1]}")
    print(f"Column Names: {list(df.columns)}")
    print("="*50)

In[5]:
def dataset_summary(df, name):
    print(f"Summary for {name} Dataset")
    print("="*50)
    print("Top 5 Rows:")
    print(df.head())
    print("\nStatistical Summary:")
    print(df.describe())
    print("\nMissing Values:")
    print(df.isnull().sum())
    print("="*50)
In[6]:
for name, df in datasets.items():
    dataset_summary(df, name)

text = " ".join(dataset1['Food'].dropna())
wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate(text)

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis('off')
plt.title('Word Cloud of Food Names - Dataset1 ')
plt.show()

dataset1['Category'].value_counts().plot.pie(autopct='%1.1f%%', figsize=(8, 8), cmap='tab20', title="Food Categories Distribution")
plt.ylabel("")
plt.show()
